<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued May 08 at 3:12PM CDT until May 08 at 4:00PM CDT by NWS Shreveport</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 400 PM CDT
FOR WEST CENTRAL MARION...NORTHWESTERN HARRISON...SOUTHEASTERN UPSHUR
AND CENTRAL GREGG COUNTIES...
At 311 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located over West Mountain,
or near Gladewater, moving east at 15 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Hail damage to vehicles is expected. Expect wind damage to
roofs, siding, and trees.
Locations impacted include...
Longview, White Oak, Gladewater, Gilmer, Clarksville City, East
Mountain, Diana, West Mountain, Union Grove, Warren City, Pritchett
and Judson.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...1.00 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
